# API Infrastructure Capacity Plan

An agent created this document to analyze whether the current
infrastructure can handle projected growth. Uses CalcMark's
built-in network, storage, and capacity planning functions.

## Current Traffic

current_rps = 8000 req/s
peak_multiplier = 3.5
peak_rps = current_rps * peak_multiplier

## Growth Projection

Traffic is growing ~12% monthly. Project 6 months out:

projected_rps = compound 8000 by 12% over 6

## Server Capacity

Size the compute tier against peak traffic with headroom:

app_servers = peak_rps at 2000 req/s per server with 25% buffer

## Database Tier

Reads are 50x writes. Size read replicas and primaries separately:

write_fraction = 2%
read_fraction = 1 - write_fraction

db_reads = 8000 * read_fraction
db_writes = 8000 * write_fraction

db_read_replicas = db_reads at 5000 per server with 20% buffer
db_primaries = db_writes at 2000 per server with 25% buffer

## Storage Performance

A typical query reads ~5 MB. Compare storage tiers:

hdd_query = seek(hdd) + read 5 MB from hdd
ssd_query = seek(ssd) + read 5 MB from ssd
nvme_query = seek(nvme) + read 5 MB from nvme

NVMe is the right choice for hot data paths.

## Latency Budget

Build a latency budget for a single API response:

network = rtt(regional)
db_query = nvme_query
app_logic = 10 ms
total_latency = network + db_query + app_logic

Under 100 ms means users perceive the response as instant.

## Daily Storage Growth

avg_payload = 2.5 KB
daily_volume = current_rps over 1 day
daily_storage = number(daily_volume) * avg_payload

compressed_daily = compress daily_storage using snappy
yearly_storage = compressed_daily * 365

yearly_storage in TB

## Bandwidth

peak_bandwidth = peak_rps over 1 second
gigabit = throughput(gigabit)
ten_gig = throughput(ten_gig)

## CDN Edge Transfer

Media transfer time from origin to CDN edge:

transfer 2 MB across continental ten_gig

## Availability Budget

Target 99.9% availability (three nines):

monthly_downtime = downtime(99.9%, month)
yearly_downtime = downtime(99.9%, year)

Each deploy takes ~5 minutes. With 8 deploys per month:

deploy_budget = 5 minutes * 8
remaining_budget = monthly_downtime - deploy_budget

## Cost Estimate

compute_monthly = $450 * app_servers
db_servers = db_read_replicas + db_primaries
db_monthly = $800 * db_servers
total_monthly = compute_monthly + db_monthly

total_monthly as napkin

## Summary

At {{current_rps}} current RPS ({{peak_rps}} peak), the system needs
{{app_servers}} app servers and {{db_read_replicas}} read replicas.
API latency budget is {{total_latency}}. Monthly infrastructure cost
is approximately {{total_monthly}}.
